caption: A little shabby on the inside, but cozy and they have yummy sandwiches and a matcha latte on the menu! Sat by the window and worked with their fast wifi and enjoyed my latte.

Don’t come here the employees  don’t listen. I asked for a bagel with cream cheese with an extra addition of bacon lettuce and tomato inside of it. When I first got my food they literally handed me a bagel with lettuce and tomato in it . It doesn’t even make sense. I asked the employee to remake it again and i told him what I originally ordered and my order was still wrong and he just put a slice of cheese and bacon on it . At that point i just gave up because i was almost late for work. Wasn’t a good experience at all ! If anything i’d rather take my money back  :((((

My girlfriend and I were looking for a quick breakfast before embarking on our journey home to Maine. Our experience at Jolt and Bolt was the perfect beginning to our odyssey. The sandwiches were built with the freshest, most delicious ingredients, accompanied with perfectly brewed coffees, and above all servers that were so pleasant and kind. Julia, my girlfriend has never seen such fresh ingredients. She barely has the words to describe how fresh and incredible she found the ingredients.
Cosy little cafe with great coffee and friendly service!
Best local cafe! Delicious sandwiches and healthy smoothie. You must try their protein boost!!!! And the Vietnamese coffee is also must try!

Love this spot, especially the cute little stone-laid alley way with tables that remind me of European cities. Lots of coffee and tea options, and the sandwiches look delicious. Great to have in the neighborhood.
Small cute place to get some healty foods & drinks, their breakfast item avocado brioche is amazing! but my fav is Acai Bowl, its more than enough for one person! Definetely I will come again!
Good atmosphere, great breakfast options and good place to do some computer work.
Smoothies are dank, affordable, but the breakfast sandwich I got once was not so good, skimpy on bacon. But they are better at coffee and baked goods

Great local coffee shop with extremely friendly staff. The coffee is great but the breakfast sandwiches are amazing! Outdoor seating is available. Perfect location for a book and a cup of coffee or to meet a friend for a quick catch up.
Cozy, hipster breakfast nook.
I really like how chill the space is. Shaded patio is perfect for outdoor coffee on a hot day. Never promises more than they can deliver.
A delight independent coffee house.
Just moved in up the block and so glad to have such a great indie coffee shop nearby. We ordered sandwiches and drinks - everything was delicious, courteous service.
coffee tea and cafe with a pleasant patio. From early am office workers to students late into the night, jolt and bolt is a neighborhood staple
Lovely coffee shop
Delish food! Yummy juice (had the carrot, beet, ginger and kale). Great service!
In the busy city,it was a pleasure to get an excellent sandwich and great coffee. The atmosphere of the cafe is relaxing and pleasant.
okay place to hang but the energy smoothie I got was chalky af
awesome prices. BEST chicken salad in DC

This is one of my favorite cafes in DC - lovely coffee, fresh food and smoothies, and the atmosphere is laid back enough that I can bring friends, books, or work with me and sit for a spell.  I love it here, and always recommend that my friends come here, especially in the summer when it's warm enough for the cute alleyway seating - love the new menu too - thank you!
Would have been a lot more pleasant if the ten dollar smoothie wasn't served in plastic cup with plastic lid and plastic straw (it wasn't to go). Also the smoothie was very icey. Staff were nice.

Really really disappointed in this place. I've been here twice and both times the server seemed unwilling to tell me if any of the options I inquired about were vegan. In fact they have surprisingly few vegan options. I wanted to like them because they're super convenient for me and have a cute alley patio. But I'm so turned off by the unfriendly service and being made to feel inconvenient for having dietary restrictions.
Avocado and cheddar on brioche is so yummy and so is the coffee! Nice service, very pleasant space. Will definitely come back.
quaint, very friendly service. stopped for a quick bfast on our way out of dc, and we thought it was nice. fresh fruit, good food, killer smoothie.

This place is a disgrace. I've stopped in twice in the last week for a smoothie 15 min before closing time. Both times I've been rudely told they're closed, and I'm automatically dismissed. I let them know it wasn't 6 pm yet but they refused to serve me. What a joke!
Quiet place conducive to working.
The best smoothies in DC. You can choose your own ingredients. The service can be a bit uneven but it’s worth it for the amazing smoothies! I love the carrot cake too.
Good food, laid back atmosphere
Great coffee and a nice spot to do remote work. I highly recommend this place!

This place is simply awful. I've had two miserable experiences there. The baristas are incredibly rude, don't smile, don't say thank you and messed up my orders both time. The coffee is no good either, and today after buying a pastry, my son bit into it and it was rancid.

I love the smoothies and overall folks are pretty friendly here. My only complaint is that I usually bring reusable mugs for my coffee and shakes so that I can save on unnecessary, single-use plastic waste. (Have you seen all the YouTube posts lately of garbage in the oceans?? So sad!) Anyway - Despite requesting that the baristas put the coffee in my mug, they always first pour it into a disposable cup and then pour it from the disposable cup to my mug. Then they toss the plastic cup away. It is such a waste and completely defeats the reason for me bringing my own mug. ☹
Service depends on their mood any given day, but doesn’t stop them from making the best chai latte in the city!
Try the mocha! Also the sweets are great too :-)
Excellent coffee, nice service.

Salami thieves at their finest. Make sure you watch the checkout as these little thieves mark things up 20-30 cents above price or just blatantly overcharge and hope you are not paying attention as they know it is a high dollar area. I've caught them a couple times. Their coffee is cheapo Costco and the food is ehh. Not going here anymore.
Place was cute but service ok and metabolic smoothie not great.

I went here a couple times during my week stay and this place has really good coffee. The pastries are okay. There's quite a bit to choose from for breakfast or snack foods and all seem to be healthy. But there is that chocolate cake that everybody likes. The staff seems to be friendly.
The service and the energy smoothie were great! I'll definitely return next time I'm in the area.
Favorite place in DC for Coffee
Quality juice/smoothies that are affordable!
Neat and tidy

I was looking for a smoothie in the neighborhood and my roommate recommended this place. It lived up to the hype she claimed it had. They had lots of varieties of smoothies and shakes (as well as pastries and coffee) and you could even build your own. I got the protein pack smoothie. It was hearty enough to be a breakfast for sure!
Slightly on the expensive side But you can make your own. So that's great

I’d like to love this place seeing as it’s 30 seconds from my apartment, but I’ve tried many a time and I’m not there.  Pros: great food and coffee, nice outdoor tables, quiet place to hang with wifi. Good selection of baked items, sandwiches, salads, fruit.  Cons: Service I’ve had has always been bare minimum, if not disinterested. It seems most times I’m in there I’m the only one ordering and it still somehow takes 15 minutes for a very standard bagel.  $5 credit card minimum, so you’ll need cash if you just want coffee.
The place is a hidden gem. Quiet spot for making some work done. They need to add “Cortado” on their coffee list though. The Lavazza coffee is perfect but they add lots of milk to the “breve.”

I was on vacation in DC and Jolt and Bolt was down the street from the condo we rented.  The first time I went in there I was hooked on their amazing coffee and muffins.  The two women that work there are amazing people, always with a friendly smile.  They made me feel like home while on vacation and not just another customer.  On my last day of vacation they gifted me a bag of their coffee grounds which warmed my heart and really hit home the type of people they are.  Washington DC is blessed to have such an amazingly run coffee joint.  If I am ever back in DC, Jolt and Bolt will again be go to spot.  Thank you ladies for making me feel like home!😊
Great place to sit and do some work. Good coffee and fast wifi.
This is one of my favorite little places. Great food and the freshest tasting smoothies in the District❤️
Great place, great coffee and excquisite sandwiches. The atmosphere is good too and Staff are good.
Nice cozy vibe, great prices and good food
Awesome food and service.  Their metabolic smoothie with spinach, protein, coffee, and quinoa oatmeal should be mass produced.
Generally sub par service
Great coffe with a smile and a nice atmosphere.
Best food, service, atmosphere, and price in this part of DC. Funny taste in music sometimes, but not too loud or offensive. Please don't let anything happen to this place.
Warm atmosphere and friendly. Healthy meal options.  Free wifi
Love this place!
My omelette was actually fluffy.
Iced chai was delicious. Food was lacking in taste. Solid music though.
Good coffee.. only place with breakfast sandwiches in the area
A hidden gem, for the outdoor seating if nothing else.
Terribly rude staff
I went less often when I saw them make the eggs for their breakfast bagels in the microwave but otherwise their drinks are great!
Great place with tasty food and good coffee. Perfect to spent some time.
My 5-star rating is for the coffee and great chill vibe

Awesome organic cafe with great coffee, smoothies, fresh squeezed juice, wraps, salads, breakfast, and free WiFi. Nice, cozy area inside for doing work or great patio outside. Definitely visit. This place is a gem and the people are very nice. Don't believe the super sensitive reviews about bad customer service. Go here!

This place is such a gem! Incredible atmosphere, very cute and homey. I come from Portland, OR, where we know our coffee shops! Great quality coffee for a great price, and a wonderful reprieve from the hot sun! Peaceful and not crowded. I know where I'm going next time I visit D.C.!
Good prices, very tasty treats. Big fan of their everything bagel with egg and cheese.
Great stop n shop with healthy prepackaged snacks. Iced coffee was good too.
Cant get over how dirty this place is.

This place is very cute and once the rush passes, not too crowded to get some work done. Everything I bought here I liked, although I'm not giving them full stars because they seem to run out of a lot of stuff. The staff was friendly and warm.

Thought about giving it a 1 star... I really want to like this place (it's small, local, hidden away), but something about this place just doesn't work for me. I've been multiple times... there's almost always a weird smell, the food prep is out in the open so one time I went and I was crying the whole time because they were chopping onions. Not a great place to work indoors either-- the music is almost always up too loud. But... on a warm day, a frozen chai latte (blended drink) in the shady alleyway seating definitely hits the spot.
Super fun
They have outdoor patio seating in a cool little alleyway
Solid place for bagels and coffee

Terrific, cute place tucked off 18th St.  They have a bunch of different drinks. from coffees to refreshing takes on lemonade.  I'll be honest, I've passed by it for years and was always put off by the awning labeling it a "juice place." It's really a cafe with fresh foods for breakfast and lunch and the people are incredibly nice.
Great little cafe
Great little cafe with a variety of pastries to choose from.

My absolute favorite café in DC. Their Chai Latte is the best I've ever had. It's a small business so uh yeah service will be a little slow for the morning rush, but they're actually really good at mediating the line, even better sometimes than places with more staff. My advice is, if you want Starbucks, then don't go other places and leave bad reviews because they aren't Starbucks.
The coffee ain't the best around, but it's got a cute atmosphere and the staff are nice. Steer clear of the food other than the breakfast sandwiches.

Unbelievably slow. Slower than any place I've ever been to. Also two of the three times I've been there, they've messed up my order. But the end result (food and drinks) is good. Please just hire more staff. I really want to like this place.
Love the egg and cheese croissants and the pies are well made

Best place to get a smoothie in town because they use fresh real fruit  not a bunch of syrup and sugar and they make a great green smoothie under $5 !! They also have many healthy options. Perfect lunch breakfast or lunch stop for those in area.
Coffee was just okay here. I like that it's a local coffee shop and cafe, but it's also a bit dirty inside. I didn't want to put my bag on the ground.

I walked into Jult and Bolt and found myself staring at a veritable cornucopia of food. a good 3rd of the coffee house is taken up by the counter surrounding the barristas, and it is covered with glass jars and display cases filled with healthy things like fruit and sandwiches. They have plenty of delicious unhealthy things, too - pastries and potato chips and the like. I also had plenty of options for coffee - less so for for tea.  Unfortunately there's not much by the way of atmosphere at Jult and Bolt. There's no music playing, and the clamour of the coffee maker is loud and constant enough that one has to raise one's voice to be heard over it. I listened to my own music (streamed over the Cafe's free wifi) and sat at  one of the 12 interior tables.  I'd recommend the place as a stop from point A to B. The cafe gives all of its decent drinks in "to go" paper cups, a la Starbucks - make use of it and go sit in Meridian park, a few blocks north and east.
